<br>
 After we buried the remains of the Teir'dal party we started out again.  The Bard Dunmire fashioned a harness for the babe Teir'dal that was now my adopted son it would appear.  I placed the child in the harness that slung from my neck and shoulders.  Once the youth was secure he reached up from his new place and pulled on my whiskers.  I looked down at the lad no slung from my neck.  He smiled at me, and it seemed that his tiny ears emitted a soft blue light.  His eyes, black as coal also seemed to emit a soft but dark light.  I sensed no evil from this child.  It was clear that these Drow were unlike the ones that I had battled in the forests of Feydark so many years ago.  There was warmth coming from my chest now that the child settled in to sleep.  I could not remove my eyes from this amazing package. Not even as the bards once again played the rhythms of travel that would carry us the rest of the way to western lands....<br>
