From the Halas Archives Tomb VII: The Wolfguard<br>
<br>
The Wolfguard had little time to spend in reunion with is family. The brothers Macalister were fast asleep in their cradle when a knock came to the chambers of Gavin and Arianna the night after his party arrived in Qeynos. Gavin opened the door to find Bandle holding an anxious Surefall Glade Ranger of Karana at arms length as he attempted to deliver his message. Gavin placed his hand on his old friend's shoulder as a sign to let the young man speak. <br>
&quot;Wolfguard, I bring news from High Hold. The Split paws have joined with the Mucktails, and are now in route to Qeynos with an army of Runnyeye, and Pickclaw Goblins supporting them.&quot; The young ranger was clearly exhausted and probably killed a dozen horses getting this message here in time for the Qeynos garrison to react. &quot; Has the Grand Duke been informed?&quot; Gavin asked the young scout. &quot;Aye my lord. One of my commrades is delivering the massage as we speak. There are also Rangers route to Halas, Surefall Glade, and to Eurdin. &quot;Have you seen the Army?&quot; Arianna asked as she came to the door behind her husband. &quot;Aye my lady, I have. It is a massive host. There must be a hundred thousand beasts heading this way. The roads are choked with the Antonican Farmers escaping the ranging host. <br>
&quot;Arianna, have Lasia watch the boys. We have to collect your father and go see the Grand Duke.&quot; Just then the entire castle shuddered with a roar. Gavin rushed to the window and could see a great white shape passing over head. The beast was on the hunt. &quot;GET THE BOYS TO THE CELLER&quot; Gavin shouted as he rushed for his armor, and weapons…Bandle crashed into the room and swept up the boys in one arm, and Arianna in the other and rushed out the door again. The Qeynos guards in the hall joined the great Halas warrior that was assigned to protect the chosen ones and joined him on his flight. Inside the rooms Gavin was finishing the last straps on his breastplate when the balcony window blew inward with a burst of frost. Gavin was knocked back off his feet and could barely see the face of the Vox as she breathed in for another bellow. Just then as Gavin began to recover, Lasia shrieked at the great white dragon and let loose a bolt of fire at its face. The dragon blinked for a second and seemed to smile at the erudite mage. Lasia was in the process of summoning when the Evil Lady responded. Lasia seemed to be frozen in time as she was struck by a column of ice that reached to the ceiling of the rooms. Gavin finally recovered and charged. As the great warrior broke through the remains of the balcony door there was a great sound of Lighting as the air around the dragon flashed. She winced at the spell that was cast by some unseen powerful wizard. Just then Gavin struck the beast across the snout with the Langseax of the Wolves leaving a great gash. Icey blue blood spilled forth covering the Wolfguard as yet another crash of lighting struck the great beast. The Vox wheeled, and ascended away from the spells and the massive blade of the Northman. Her wings beat over the castle and created a hurricane of snow that further blinded Gavin…the Wolfguard stumbled as he tried to maintain his balance in the gale force winds. Once the Vox was aloft she shouted down.. &quot;This night I give to you Macalisters, but you shall feel my wrath Arianna, and you Wolfguard will burn in my pits for the mark you have left upon me.&quot; She great lady turned north and was gone. Gavin once again rushed out to the balcony to track the Dragons heading. She was heading back to her lair. Gavin turned to the nanny that so lovingly cared for his sons, and was the companion of his wife. She lay horribly burned on the floor in a lifeless heap. Arianna and Bastin floated down to he balcony accompanied by several other casters from the Qeynos Casters Guild. They had pirched themselves on the rooftops of the castle and were responsible for the massive lighting strikes that finally warded off the great dragon. Arianna shreiked at the sight of her friend and rushed to see if there was anything that could be done, but it was clearly to late for the brave Eurdite woman. She had been called home to her maker.<br>
